divs: Sighting Details I was taking a walk at a local school taking pics of sunset late one evening. I took many pics that night of the sunset at varying degrees of light and cloud cover. I packed up and went home not realizing what I shot. About a month later I finally uploaded the images into my computer. About a week after the upload I was photo shopping my images to post on the web. I came across this image and noted a dark spot near the top. After zooming in I realized it looked like an ufo. At first I thought it would be an airplane. I fully expected to find wings attached to the main image but those never materialized. The first time I noticed the image was when I was uploading pics to the web. Upon zooming in I noticed there were no airplane wings attached so I looked again and shouted," Holy cr*p, HONEY!! come here". I asked her what she thought. Of course I was or am excited. I always like to second guess myself so I called in my girlfriend for a second opinion. Her opinion is that it is a ufo. It does not look like a weather balloon or a plane or anything else. She thinks its a ufo.
